					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The ends of lines are lost. The inscription seems to record an endowment of land at the village [Tuhiri] made by the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭavar</hi> of Vañji-nāḍu for worship in the temple of Nāṭṭīśvara built by <hi rend="bold">Śāttaṉ Karuvūr</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kannaradēva-Māyilaṭṭi</hi> of Tuvaḷai. This is probably an inscription of the time of the <hi rend="bold">Koṅgu king Vikrama-Chōḷa</hi> (see No. 28 above).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
